body:
“I think she’s immediately envious because Daenerys is more beautiful and younger than she is and the prophecy says somebody younger and more beautiful will take her place so I’m sure that’s at the forefront of her mind. And Tyrion is her Hand, so she couldn’t be any worse.”_Lena Headey

title: A Dragon Raised Snow: Chapter 1-20
body:
Some people keep asking me for the link to the wattpad version, so here you go.

https://www.wattpad.com/story/144909741-a-dragon-raised-snow

Story summary: What if Ned told Jon the truth before he left for the nights watch? Jon doesn’t join the night’s watch but instead travels to Essos in search of his family (Daenerys and Viserys). Things don’t go to plan and Jon ends up becoming a sellsword and travels Essos. He meets some familiar faces and some new faces. But eventually he finds what he is looking for and it wasn’t what he expected.

summary: Jon Snow is meant to portray the role of Jesus Christ
title: Jon Snow is meant to portray the role of Jesus Christ
body:
now hear me out:

Jesus:

  • was wrongfully presumed to be of low birth (son of carpenter)
  • depicted as befriending Children
  • betrayed by his disciple Judas
  • was murdered and rose from the dead
  • was teaching to “love your neighbour as you love yourself”
  • Quote from the Bible “the last enemy that shall be destroyed is death”

Jon Snow:

  • was wrongfully presumed to be of low birth (bastard)
  • befriended Arya (also gave her a goodbye gift) and Olly
  • betrayed by Night’s Watch - including his “disciple” Olly
  • was murdered and rose from the dead
  • encouraged the Night’s Watch to welcome the Wildlings aka to “love their neighbours”
  • refers to the White Walkers as “the dead” who are thought to be their last and biggest enemy

Conclusion: Jon Snow = Jesus
